# 16. If Too Many Adapters Were Added

If the command was run multiple times by accident, extra adapters can appear.

To remove one, first list interfaces:

```bash
virsh domiflist windows10
```

Then remove the wrong one by MAC address:

```bash
virsh detach-interface \
  --domain windows10 \
  --type network \
  --mac XX:XX:XX:XX:XX:XX \
  --config \
  --live
```

What it does:

```text
Removes the selected virtual network adapter from the VM.
```

```text
--mac
```

selects the exact adapter to remove.

Final goal:

```text
Only one default adapter
Only one vsroisolated adapter
```

---

